  "time_ut": 1657122553,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0d82\u0da0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9a \u0db4\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dab\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0da7 8.8\u0d9a \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "8.8 percent growth in tourist arrivals",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "To promote the tourism industry amid the fuel crisis, the Ministry of Tourism has implemented a new program with the support of the Sri Lanka Transport Board and the Sri Lanka Army. According to Tourism and Lands Minister Mr. Harin Fernando, the drivers registered with the Ministry of Tourism will be given the required fuel after calling the given hotline numbers and giving their itinerary.",
        "The minister said this today (05) while joining the press conference held at the government news department auditorium to inform the people about the tourism industry revival plan and the upcoming programs of the Ministry of Lands.",
        "Out of the three thousand calls received so far, arrangements have been made to provide fuel to about a thousand drivers. It is also possible to get the coupon they want by visiting the Sri Lanka Tourism Development Authority office and giving the relevant information. Fuel will not be issued by providing only one's tourist ID.",
        "There is an increase of 8.8% in the arrival of tourists this month compared to last month. Despite the crisis, tourists are coming and by the coming month of August, it is expected that a large number of devotees from countries like India, France and England will visit the festival at Nallur temple. And by December, which is the winter season, the arrival of tourists will increase.",
        "The Ministry of Lands is working to provide a large amount of land for crop cultivation. Under the leadership of the Prime Minister, the granting of freehold deeds for licensed lands will take place in the future. The Prime Minister's Office is already preparing the necessary legal work to implement it. In allotment of land, special attention is given to special projects like crop cultivation, hotel projects, investment related projects."
      ],
